@NODE "Main" "»LhaSave/LhaLoad« for Finalwriter"
@TOC "MAIN"
                               @{fg shine}»LhaSave/LhaLoad 1.1e«@{fg text}

are FREEWARE ARexx-Scripts for Finalwriter to save and load FW-Documents 
                           as .lha-file.


                           @{" " link "Brauch"} Requirements

                           @{" " link "Install"} Installation

                           @{" " link "Benutz"} How to use

                           @{" " link "Sonst"} Author

                           @{" " link "Hist"} History

                           @{" " link "Future"} Future

 Sorry, for my poor english. If you want, you can translate my german guide
 and send to me. You can find the german guide in the Aminet.

 Thanks.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Brauch" "Requirements"
@TOC "MAIN"



   - FinalWriter
     FinalCopy, i dont know if all ARexx commands work

   - RexxMast

   - RexxReqTools.library (© Rafael D`Halleweyn - latest version: 37.95)
        available:
            Aminet( 9) - text/edit/CedASIF.lha
            Aminet(10) - util/rexx/varexx.lha
            Aminet(11) - comm/tcp/amiconnect.lha
            Aminet(12) - comm/fido/xpack275.lha
            Aminet(13) - util/libs/ReqToolUsr.lha
            Aminet(15) - util/libs/ReqToolUsr.lha

   - ReqTools.library     (© Nico François      - latest version: 38.1443)
        available:
            Aminet - util/libs/ReqToolUsr.lha

   - c:Delete             (© Amiga Technologies)
   - c:lha V1.38          (© Stefan Boberg 1991/92)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"



1. Copy »LhaSave.fwrexx« and »LhaLoad.fwrexx« in your FWMacros-Drawer.

2. Start programm »RexxMast«.

3. Start »Finalwriter«.

4. Open menu "Layout - Preferences...". ??? (Sorry, but i use the german 
                                             version)

         * "Benutzerbefehle"
         * "Benutzerbefehlleiste - Befehlleiste 2"
         * move "Schalter" in "Befehle" 
         * "Befehl" - "Typ" - ARexx-Script
         * "Befehl" - "Auswählen" (LhaLoad.fwrexx)

   Please look at yout FW-manual to install macros.

5. Install also »LhaSave.fwrexx«

6. Save

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Benutz" "How to use"
@TOC "MAIN"

  @{fg shine} Save @{fg text}

          If you want to save your document, use the button for
          »LhaSave.fwrexx«.
          Look at @{" Installation " link "Install"}.

          The normal document will be saving. Then it will be 
          lha-crunching. [Filename]@{fg shine}.fwlha@{fg text}

  @{fg shine} Load @{fg text}

          If you want to load your crunched document, use the 
          button for »LhaLoad.fwrexx«.
          Look at @{" Installation " link "Install"}.

          Select your @{fg shine}.fwlha@{fg text}-file.
          It will be loading automatically.

                                   Thats all.


@ENDNODE

